But how did we get here?

00:43:05.869 --> 00:43:08.869
We learned from the example of Paul

00:43:08.869 --> 00:43:12.869
and how he thoroughly preached the good news.

00:43:12.869 --> 00:43:24.070
The group overseer could have simply listed what changes were needed

00:43:24.070 --> 00:43:26.070
to improve the family's ministry.

00:43:26.070 --> 00:43:32.070
Instead, he directed the father to a specific principle found in the scriptures.

00:43:32.070 --> 00:43:39.070
After all, it is only God's word that is inspired for teaching.

00:43:39.070 --> 00:43:42.070
Bible translations in common languages

00:43:42.070 --> 00:43:45.070
started to spread across Europe in the 1500s.

00:43:45.070 --> 00:43:48.070
But it took much longer for more remote places

00:43:48.070 --> 00:43:51.070
to receive the Bible.

00:43:51.070 --> 00:43:56.070
It was in 1766 that the complete Greek scriptures

00:43:56.070 --> 00:44:00.070
or New Testament was first published in Greenlandic,

00:44:00.070 --> 00:44:05.070
a language spoken today by about 50,000 people.

00:44:05.070 --> 00:44:07.070
In August of last year,

00:44:07.070 --> 00:44:11.070
I had the privilege of serving a regional convention in Greenland,

00:44:11.070 --> 00:44:14.070
which is overseen by the Scandinavia branch.

00:44:14.070 --> 00:44:17.070
Greenland is the neighbor to the north of Newfoundland,

00:44:17.070 --> 00:44:20.070
where I pioneered for 11 years.

00:44:20.070 --> 00:44:25.070
So it was a wonderful experience to go there and meet our brothers.

00:44:25.070 --> 00:44:29.070
Some 400 brothers and sisters traveled at their own expense

00:44:29.070 --> 00:44:34.070
from all over Scandinavia to support the convention in Greenland.

00:44:34.070 --> 00:44:38.070
Although Greenland is a land covered by large ice caps,

00:44:38.070 --> 00:44:43.070
there are many warm hearts yearning for the truth.

00:44:43.070 --> 00:44:57.989
I think that Jesus had Greenland in mind when he spoke about preaching

00:44:57.989 --> 00:45:01.989
to the most distant part of the earth.

00:45:01.989 --> 00:45:03.989
My name is Arna Matson.

00:45:03.989 --> 00:45:07.989
My wife Karen and I have lived in Greenland for more than 34 years.

00:45:07.989 --> 00:45:11.989
We have traveled all over the country preaching about God's kingdom

00:45:11.989 --> 00:45:15.989
and we have had some fantastic experiences.

00:45:15.989 --> 00:45:21.989
In the 1950s, two young special pioneers came to Greenland as the first publishers.

00:45:21.989 --> 00:45:24.989
They traveled by boat from town to town,

00:45:24.989 --> 00:45:27.989
carrying just tents and simple equipment.

00:45:27.989 --> 00:45:32.989
They had to endure the cold weather, face resistance from the local ministers,

00:45:32.989 --> 00:45:36.989
and even fight with sledge dogs that took their food.

00:45:36.989 --> 00:45:42.989
But they laid the groundwork for the great effort that has been made to preach to all in this country.

00:45:43.989 --> 00:45:50.989
In the 1960s and 70s, many families moved here from Denmark to help with the preaching work.

00:45:50.989 --> 00:45:57.989
I remember how I as a teenager in 1971 moved from Denmark to Greenland with my family.

00:45:57.989 --> 00:46:00.989
It was not easy to learn the language,

00:46:00.989 --> 00:46:06.989
but the brothers and sisters from Denmark did their best and it had a good effect on the territory.

00:46:07.989 --> 00:46:11.989
In 1973, the watchtower began to be published in Greenlandic.

00:46:11.989 --> 00:46:14.989
Just to pronounce the name,

00:46:14.989 --> 00:46:18.989
Nabazoliak, Alabama, Suifik, was a challenge.

00:46:18.989 --> 00:46:22.989
But it has been a popular magazine in Greenland ever since.

00:46:22.989 --> 00:46:29.369
Once we met a couple who for many years had received copies of the watchtower

00:46:29.369 --> 00:46:32.369
when publishers visited their settlement.

00:46:32.369 --> 00:46:36.369
They told us that they often felt depressed when they woke up in the morning.

00:46:38.369 --> 00:46:44.369
But when they read the magazine, they felt better, and they would read the same copies over and over again.

00:46:44.369 --> 00:46:53.960
When the temperature drops and there's no falls,

00:46:53.960 --> 00:46:58.960
the landscape gets covered by a beautiful white blanket for half a year.

00:46:58.960 --> 00:47:03.429
So the publishers make good use of the summer.

00:47:03.429 --> 00:47:07.429
Some towns and settlements only seldom receive a witness.

00:47:07.429 --> 00:47:12.429
There are no roads between the towns, but we reach isolated areas by boats.

00:47:12.429 --> 00:47:17.429
When someone shows interest in our message, the contact is maintained by phone.

00:47:17.429 --> 00:47:21.059
Many have great respect for the Bible,

00:47:21.059 --> 00:47:27.059
and so my book of Bible stories has found its way into many, many homes.

00:47:27.059 --> 00:47:30.059
Over a period of 24 years,

00:47:30.059 --> 00:47:35.059
Karen and I have sailed so much that it equals a trip twice around the globe.

00:47:35.059 --> 00:47:37.059
This has caused a lot of effort and money,

00:47:37.059 --> 00:47:39.059
but with Jehovah's blessing,

00:47:39.059 --> 00:47:42.059
we have been able to continue year after year

00:47:42.059 --> 00:47:45.059
preaching to the distant parts of Greenland.

00:47:45.059 --> 00:47:53.809
The preaching work here is a great experience.

00:47:53.809 --> 00:47:56.809
People are attentive and kind,

00:47:56.809 --> 00:48:00.809
but it took a long time before the first native Greenlander was baptized,

00:48:00.809 --> 00:48:04.809
actually 18 years of zealous preaching.

00:48:04.809 --> 00:48:12.760
Today there are more than 150 publishers in five congregations.

00:48:12.760 --> 00:48:27.940
Jehovah has really blessed the work that has been done here for more than 60 years.

00:48:27.940 --> 00:48:29.940
In August 2016,

00:48:29.940 --> 00:48:34.940
a very special convention was held in the capital of Munich.

00:48:34.940 --> 00:48:37.940
Brothers and sisters from all over Scandinavia

00:48:37.940 --> 00:48:45.489
